Hello, friends.

This is how *I* set up TL in Fedora:

I have /opt/bin which actually points to 
/usr/local/texlive/<year>/bin/<arch>; this means I only need to update 
the symlink when installing new TL versions.

I have the following script living inside /etc/profile.d:

=====================================
#!/bin/bash
pathmunge () {
	if ! echo $PATH | /bin/egrep -q "(^|:)$1($|:)" ; then
		if [ "$2" = "after" ] ; then
			PATH=$PATH:$1
		else
			PATH=$1:$PATH
		fi
	fi
}
pathmunge /opt/texbin
unset pathmunge
=====================================

TL binaries are then set on path systemwide. Different approach from 
.bashrc (userwide), but both ideas converge.

And that is pretty much it.

I never ran into problems with TL in Fedora. We might need a couple of 
extra info, so we could track down the errors.

All the best,

